{"title": "We Would Have Told You, But...", "content": "Sherlock Holmes, \"The Adventure of the Dying Detective\" , \"The Adventure of the Dying Detective\" \"You won't be offended, Watson? You will realize that among your many talents dissimulation finds no place, and that if you had shared my secret you would never have been able to impress Smith with the urgent necessity of his presence, which was the vital point of the whole scheme.\"\n\nAn episode in which a main character and the audience are kept in the dark by the character's friends or colleagues. This is to pull off a sting against someone else, never a main character.\n\nThey will be given the excuse at the end... \"We would have told you, but we needed your reactions to look genuine.\" In settings that include telepathy it's often done to foil even that.\n\nA character who just loves to keep others intrigued may sometimes use this as a pretext.\n\nIt's a Not Himself with the numbers inverted.\n\nWhen this is done to the actors, it is Enforced Method Acting. Compare Locked Out of the Loop.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeWouldHaveToldYouBut", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SherlockHolmes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FruitsBasket", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JojosBizarreAdventureStardustCrusaders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/SailorMoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BlackCanary", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/GreenArrow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheFlash", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/IronMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/JudgeDredd", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/LowLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheSimpingDetective", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Chicago", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheDarkKnight", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IndependenceDay", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ColdfireTrilogy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DiogenesClub", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SorcererCon